<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-22T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-22T16:00:00-05:00" n="478" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d478">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2385: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Tenney</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-22T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September
                                            22, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Your August 26, 6 p.m.</p>
                            <p>Please ascertain and advise the Department as precisely as possible
                                what powers have been entrusted to Hsu En Yuan. It is particularly
                                desired to know whether he is authorized to renew the existing
                                Chicago Bank loan of $5,000,000<note n="17" xml:id="d478fn17">See
                                        <ref target="frus1916#pg_138"><hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>,
                                        1916, pp. 138</ref>–<ref target="frus1916#pg_143">143</ref>.</note> and whether he is empowered to negotiate for
                                the supplementary loan of $25,000,000 contemplated by the
                                contract.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>